# persona-pulse uses PER-PERSONA secrets: copy deploy/persona.env.example to
# secrets/<persona>.env instead of filling this file (see README "Setup").
#
# A repo-level .env still works as a shared-defaults layer (loaded first; the persona's
# secrets/<name>.env overrides it for `pulse supervise`), and is where non-persona knobs like
# PULSE_DASHBOARD_PORT can live. Never commit either file.

# PULSE_DASHBOARD_HOST=127.0.0.1
# PULSE_DASHBOARD_PORT=8440
